headline: Franklin Templeton Institute Forecasts Broadening Global Opportunities Amid Monetary Easing and Dollar Weakness in 2026
summary: SAN MATEO, Calif., November 18, 2025--The Franklin Templeton Institute today released its Global Investment Outlook: 2026 and Beyond, highlighting three key cyclical themes for investors that underscore changing global dynamics and shifting avenues for return.

headline: Treasury Yields Fall as U.S. Labor Data Gets Updated
summary: TREASURYS 0854 ET – Treasury yields fall amid a global stocks selloff and signs of labor softness in delayed U.S. data. Worries around tech stocks trigger risk aversion around the world, following Monday’s losses.
